---
// Imports.
import "../../styles/privacy-policy.css";

// Components.
import Layout from '../../layouts/base.astro';
---
<Layout title="Delete Account - CyberAlerts" currentPage="">
	<section class="policy-content">
		<article>
			<h4>Delete Your CyberAlerts Account</h4>
			<p>This page explains how to request deletion of your CyberAlerts account and associated data, in line with Google Play's data deletion requirements.</p>

			<h5>How to Delete Your Account</h5>
			<p>You can delete your CyberAlerts account directly within the app:</p>
			<ol>
				<li>Open the CyberAlerts app</li>
				<li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong></li>
				<li>Select <strong>Delete Account</strong></li>
				<li>Confirm the deletion when prompted</li>
			</ol>
			<p>Once confirmed, you will be signed out immediately and your account will be scheduled for deletion.</p>

			<h5>What Gets Deleted</h5>
			<p>Deleting your account removes:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Your account and authentication details (email, sign-in method)</li>
				<li>Your quiz progress, badges, streaks, and daily challenge history</li>
				<li>Any other data associated with your account within the app</li>
			</ul>

			<h5>Retention</h5>
			<p>Your data is deleted immediately upon confirmation.</p>

			<h5>Need Help?</h5>
			<p>If you're unable to access the app or need help with your deletion request, contact us at cyberfocus@code-prem.dev.</p>
		</article>
	</section>
</Layout>